    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've added some unit tests, but before putting in a PR it looks like there are some other issues at play.\r\n\r\nThe original regression around -1 being passed for the block number to get the latest causing a buffer underflow is resolved by the code changes in #4528 and #4635 but because we create a fresh oracle for every RPC request the default price will always be returned (0 based on the default config in `ethconfig.Defaults.GPO`).  It looks like this is the problem found in #4630.  \r\n\r\nThe oracle code is doing a few locks/checks around reading the cached value which won't exist as we have a fresh instance every time so could we take this chance to fix up the Oracle to skip the cache checks and let the ethAPI code handle holding on to the last known good gas price in a cache of its own?",
